export default "# Performance Work Statement (PWS)\\\r\n\\\r\n**Project Title:** [Insert Title]\\\r\n**Agency/Office:** [Insert Name]\\\r\n**Solicitation/Contract Number:** [Insert #]\\\r\n**Date:** [MM/DD/YYYY]\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 1. Introduction\\\r\n\\\r\nBriefly describe the agency's mission and the reason for this\r\nacquisition.\\\r\n**Example:**\\\r\nThe [Agency/Office] is acquiring contractor support to design, build,\r\nand deliver a modern digital service that improves [mission/business\r\nprocess]. This support will be delivered using agile, user-centered,\r\nand modular development practices.\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 2. Background\\\r\n\\\r\nSummarize the history, legacy system context (if any), prior efforts, or\r\nkey drivers leading to this requirement.\\\r\n**Example:**\\\r\nThe current [system/process] is outdated, inflexible, and does not\r\nmeet user needs. A prior modernization attempt resulted in partial\r\ndelivery but failed to integrate user feedback or adapt to changing\r\nrequirements. This contract seeks to reset the approach using iterative\r\ndelivery.\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 3. Objectives\\\r\n\\\r\nState the mission-aligned goals this effort must achieve.\\\r\n\\\r\n**Examples:**\\\r\n\\\r\n- Deliver a minimum viable product (MVP) that enables [user goal]\\\r\n- Improve system usability, accessibility, and data quality\\\r\n- Support continuous user research and testing\\\r\n- Transition full capability and knowledge to government staff\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 4. Scope of Work\\\r\n\\\r\nDescribe what's in scope---functions, services, and deliverables. Avoid\r\nprescribing \"how.\"\\\r\n**Example:**\\\r\nThe contractor shall provide all necessary services, labor, tools, and\r\nmaterials to:\\\r\n\\\r\n- Conduct user research and journey mapping\\\r\n- Design and prototype new service features\\\r\n- Develop, test, and deploy working software in iterations\\\r\n- Conduct backlog grooming and sprint planning with the Product Owner\\\r\n- Provide cloud architecture guidance and DevSecOps support\\\r\n- Create and maintain documentation and training materials\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 5. Tasks and Deliverables\\\r\n\\\r\nDefine major tasks and what's expected from the contractor. Use tables\r\nfor clarity.\\\r\n\\\r\n\\| Task # \\| Task Description \\| Deliverables \\| Due Date or Frequency\r\n\\|\\\r\n\\|--------\\|--------------------\\|-------------------------------------\\|------------------------\\|\\\r\n\\| 1 \\| Discovery & Planning \\| Research plan, stakeholder interviews\r\nsummary \\| 2 weeks after kickoff \\|\\\r\n\\| 2 \\| MVP Development \\| Working software deployed to staging \\| End\r\nof Sprint 3 \\|\\\r\n\\| 3 \\| Usability Testing \\| Test report & recommended changes \\| Every\r\n2 sprints \\|\\\r\n\\| 4 \\| Transition Support \\| Final code handoff, tech documentation \\|\r\nEnd of base period \\|\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 6. Schedule\\\r\n\\\r\nProvide the base and any option periods.\\\r\n\\\r\n**Example:**\\\r\n\\\r\n- Base Period: 6 months from date of award\\\r\n- Option Period 1: 6 months\\\r\n- Option Period 2: 6 months\\\r\n\\\r\nSprints will be two-week increments unless otherwise modified.\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 7. Performance Standards\\\r\n\\\r\nSet the bar for what acceptable performance looks like. This feeds into\r\nthe QASP.\\\r\n\\\r\n\\| Performance Area \\| Standard \\| Acceptable Quality Level (AQL) \\|\r\nSurveillance Method \\|\\\r\n\\|------------------\\|----------------------------------\\|---------------------------------\\|--------------------------------\\|\\\r\n\\| Code delivery \\| Meets DoD coding guidelines, passes review \\| 95% of\r\ndeliverables \\| Automated + manual review \\|\\\r\n\\| User research \\| Conducted every sprint cycle \\| 100% compliance \\|\r\nPO sign-off \\|\\\r\n\\| Accessibility \\| WCAG 2.1 AA compliance \\| 100% \\| Pa11y scan &\r\nmanual \\|\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 8. Place of Performance\\\r\n\\\r\n**Example:**\\\r\n\\\r\n- Primarily remote\\\r\n- Occasional in-person meetings in [City, State]\\\r\n- Staging and production deployments to FedRAMP-approved environments\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 9. Security Requirements\\\r\n\\\r\nSpecify clearance, system access, or data handling requirements.\\\r\n\\\r\n**Examples:**\\\r\n\\\r\n- All work must be performed within CONUS\\\r\n- Contractors must complete agency security training within 10 business\r\ndays\\\r\n- No classified information will be handled\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\n## 10. Government-Furnished Resources\\\r\n\\\r\nList tools, systems, access, or data the Government will provide.\\\r\n\\\r\n**Examples:**\\\r\n\\\r\n- Existing backlog and user research artifacts\\\r\n- Access to product owner and stakeholders\\\r\n- Government cloud environments (e.g., Cloud.gov, AWS GovCloud)\\\r\n\\\r\n---\\\r\n\\\r\nLet me know if you want this turned into a Word template, tailored for a\r\nspecific contract type (e.g., FFP per iteration, T&M), or linked to a\r\nspecific QASP or SOO.\r\n"